  independent woman and not subject to the X-Change Free Use Act.  People soon began to refer to the loops as "Halos" and
  everyone soon understood that its wearer should be treated with dignity and respect.  Unless she requests otherwise, that is.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  The integrated lock securing the loop in place can only be removed by border officials when exiting the country, with a
  replacement secured to her upon her return.  Or it can be removed and replaced at special government offices for sizing or
  style adjustments.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  And removal is also done for women that voluntarily enroll in the Free Use Program, either temporarily or permanently.
