::ReeducationFreeUseEmployment
<<nobr>>
  <h1>Employment and Economic Environment</h1>
  Thanks to record high worker productivity since the enactment of Free-Use laws, the economy of Freedonia has been booming.
  That, combined with the lucrative tourism industry also helps fund the Free-Use Program while minimizing the tax burden on
  the citizens.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  <img src="PartX/Reeducation47.jpg" hspace="10" vspace="10" height="600" align="left">
  For women on permanent or long-term Free-Use contracts, job placement services are available through local Free-Use Program
  offices.  Temporary assignments can also be provided for those on short-term contracts, though generally this is not needed
  as those women tend to remain at their same employer or educational institution.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  The primary job duties always include being available for use whenever desired.  However other duties, compatible with the
  assignees skills and interests, may also be assigned if they do not interfere with her primary duties.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  Care is taken to ensure job placements spread the benefits of the Free-Use Program across the entire economic spectrum
  of Freedonia.  Gone are the days where the CEO has a wife, a mistress, and a secretary, all for his exclusive use, while
  most of his workers spend their few hours of lesuire time lonely.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  To maximize reproductive opportunities for Freedonian citizens, Free-Use participants unable to conceive, due to an existing
  pregnancy or for another reason, are often assigned to serve in one of the tourist enclaves within Freedonia.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  Most job assignments do not require a full 40 hours each week at a fixed job.  More common is a 20/20 split.  Where 20 hours
  is spent on a defined assignment, and 20 hours are left as public lesuire time for the assignee.  She can engage in whatever
  lesuire pursuits she wishes, so long as she is in a public location and available for use.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  The remainder of her time, including two days off each week, can be used as she wishes.  These days vary from assignment
  to assignment, ensuring adequate availability throughout the week.  She can remain at home and rest if she wishes on these days,
  available only to anyone sharing her living arrangements or visting at her home.  She can also venture out into public as she
  desires, though she is still available for use if desired, and the time does not count towards her work hours.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  <video src="Part10/StripBartender.mp4" autoplay loop muted height="500"></video><br>
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  Additionally, women on longer contracts accrue [[vacation time|ReeducationFreeUseVacation]] throughout the year.
<</nobr>>

::ReeducationFreeUseVacation
