  These vacation days can be used in one of three ways, they can be used to travel internationally.
  They can be used within Freedonia, with no public availability requirement and a temporary "Halo" assigned. Or,
  they can be used within the country, in a vacation destination of her choosing, but a 20 hour per week public availability
  requirement and no assigned Halo.  Travel expenses are subsidized for women choosing the third option, which is the most
  commonly used option.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  <div style="float:left;padding:12px;">
    <video src="PartX/Reeducation48.webm" autoplay loop muted height="500"></video>
  </div>
<</nobr>>
<<nobr>>
  Travel to to select international destinations during your vacation days is allowed for any woman on a long-term Free-Use
  contract.  These select internation destinations are countries that recognize the validity of our Free-Use contracts and
  have extradition agreements with Freedonia to arrange for the return of anyone that fails to return from international
  travel in breach of their contract.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  Women on a short-term contract, of course, can travel freely to any destination they wish once their contract term
  has ended.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  A popular choice for many women are select cruise lines and all-inclusive resorts that offer free or subsidized
  accommodations for those agreeing to make themselves available while on their vacation as they would at home.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  A current list of allowed countries and participating cruise lines and resorts is available online or at your
  local Free-Use Program office.
<</nobr>>

<<nobr>>
  (*) Note:
<</nobr>>
<<nobr>>
  Travel options may be more limited to those with a criminal record, as many countries will deny entry based on
